{{!--
  VCarve Pro post — wood routing on Mach3-class controllers (Laguna Swift, etc.)

  Tuned for the **VCarve Pro environment** in WorkTrackCAM:
  - Wood-routing-friendly spindle warmup (G4 dwell after M3)
  - Conservative safe Z (uses machine.workAreaMm.z)
  - Mach3-style program tape markers (% on first/last lines)
  - Dust-collection M-code commented out — uncomment if your control wires it
  - No peck cycles by default; drill ops emit explicit Z moves
  - Single-tool program by default — extend if you wire ATC into your Laguna

  Lines starting with ";" are operator-visible comments in the output file.
  Template context keys: resources/posts/README.md (PostContext / renderPost).
--}}
