; Wood routing checklist:
; [1] Material clamped flat to spoilboard, no warps under bit path
; [2] Tool-length set: V-bit at sharp tip, end mill at flute bottom, drill at tip
; [3] WCS X0/Y0 at workpiece corner per VCarve Pro setup; Z0 = top of stock
; [4] Dust collection ON (uncomment M7/M8 line below if your post wires it)
; [5] Air-cut first: spindle off, Z high, 25–50% feed override
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): {{machine.workAreaMm.x}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.y}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.z}}
{{#if machine.maxSpindleRpm}}; Spindle max: {{machine.maxSpindleRpm}} RPM
{{/if}}{{#if operationLabel}}; Operation: {{operationLabel}}
{{/if}}; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
{{units}}        ; G21=mm / G20=inch — must match controller defaults at power-on
G90              ; absolute distance mode
G17              ; XY plane (typical for G2/G3 arcs)
G94              ; feed in units/min
{{#if wcsLine}}; Active work offset — verify fixture zero matches G54–G59 selection
{{wcsLine}}
{{/if}}; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Spindle on (dialect snippet — Mach3 emits M3 S<rpm>)
{{spindleOn}}
G4 P2.0          ; dwell 2 s for spindle to reach commanded RPM (wood router warmup)
; M7              ; coolant/mist OFF — uncomment if your control uses M7 for dust
; M8              ; flood coolant — typically OFF for wood; uncomment for wet ops
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
{{#each toolpathLines}}
{{this}}
{{/each}}
